			<p>A really intriguing post. This is one of my favorite stories by Bolano &#8212; shadowy, wrecked, monstrous, and yet weirdly understated. I think of it almost as being a short film, one by Maddin or Jack Smith, almost as if the story wants us to see it in other mediums, the &#8220;innumerable media&#8221; you discuss.</p>
