						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-5183" title="">October 2nd, 2012 on 7:57 pm</a> </small>

			<p>@Lucas: woah that&#8217;s really cool. thanks for the link.I like how hallucination, magical-thinking creep back up even through something that I considered to be stable,such as names!<br />
@Rawbbie: your point about voyeurism is a really good one; voyeur requires that one&#8217;s vision is in both state of visible and invisible. it reminds me of Kim Kiduk&#8217;s Bad Guy  (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bad_Guy_(film)" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bad_Guy_(film)</a> ) where the camera&#8217;s vision oscillate between voyeuristic protagonist&#8217;s vision and &#8220;reality&#8221;, what is actually happening.</p>
			</div><div class="cleared"></div><!-- clears the floats so the backgrounds show all the way down -->
		</li>

	
	
		<li id="comment-5184">


<a class="gravatar">
<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/43b3cd2f0e91e546df54bde99b332ff6?s=69&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2Fmontevidayo.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fpixeled%2Fimages%2Fgravatar-trans.png&#038;r=x' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/43b3cd2f0e91e546df54bde99b332ff6?s=138&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2Fmontevidayo.com%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2Fpixeled%2Fimages%2Fgravatar-trans.png&#038;r=x 2x' class='avatar avatar-69 photo' height='69' width='69' /></a>

			<div class="commentbody">
			<cite>Jiyoon</cite> 
						<br />

			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-5184" title="">October 2nd, 2012 on 8:44 pm</a> </small>

			<p>@Joyelle yes I love  that line “Pajarito Gómez emanated prostatic fluid!”! I also meant to mention how Pajarito expands into the room and to the world in the part that describes him as  “mineral”, “Stonelike ” and his  “prick” “transparent”. This moment reminds meof  Zurita’s poem in purgatory (this one is available online <a href="http://www.poetryfoundation.org/poem/239978" rel="nofollow">http://www.poetryfoundation.org/poem/239978</a> ) in which the infinite desert, its oppressive vastness turns transparent (absent-present); metastability/acting as both solid and fluid, pregnant with death.</p>
			</div><div class="cleared"></div><!-- clears the floats so the backgrounds show all the way down -->
		</li>

	
	
